rComments: I took 2362 and 3104 and she is an amazing prof. By far my favourite Ive had. She does give you book reports, and so I would suggest you to read and buy the texts. The final essay is usually based on your class notes, so its better to attend and take detailed notes so you get a better grade on the final exam.

Put bluntly, this class made me fall in love with Canadian history. Lots of writing (3 book reviews and a pretty big take-home final paper), but there were no exams. Her lectures are interesting, and she gives excellent feedback on papers. It's not too hard to get an A if you're good with papers, and put in the effort

rComments: Prof St-Onge was much better than expected. I was a bit worried about the class as I had never taken a HIS course before. Three papers and a final take home exam. Highly recommend her!

Content wise the course was pretty straightforward: 3 book reviews and a take-home final. She assigned the first two books, but let us choose the last one. If you're not a strong writer this class might be a challenge. But there's hope: by following her thorough feedback I went from getting a B on the first essay to an A on the final one.

rComments: She is a great prof and the lectures are relatively interesting but if you are taking her class expect to work. In her class we had to read three textbooks and write papers on each one and the final was a hand in of three essays. I would definitely recommend the class but only if you are willing to put in the work.

super bonne prof! tres facile a suivre et clair dans ces attentes!  les travaux sont 3 compte rendu d'un libre donc soyer pres a lire MAIS les livres son super facile et interressant! la matiere quelle enseigne es super intereassant et facile a suivre, fait vraiment une histoire de tout le canada, pas seulement sur l'ontario et le quebec
